Defendant Adam J Brownell in court with Attorney Patrick Cavanaugh Brennan.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Natalie Schiferl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called for sentencing hearing.  State gives sentencing recommendations and files victim impact statements.  Victim makes statements.  Attorney Brennan makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9  MONTHS HUBER  (2 days credit)

TERM OF PROBATION:   18 MONTHS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No VIOLENT contact with: victim or any family member

COSTS:  $343.00  (to be paid out of cash bail posted)

CONDITION TIME:  60 Days - 30 Days Straight time and last 30 days with huber - ALL STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion


